{"build_type":"executable","description":"The single JSON-native shell door. Reads a json request from argv[2] (-c style, argv[1] is the -c flag slot) or stdin; parses it; the request is a single-key object {\"<tool>\": <arg>} where the one key names the tool and its value is the tool's argument. If it is not a valid object, has no first member, or the member has no key (e.g. an array), emit the usage/tools help error. Otherwise resolve the key to a pinned tool and execve it, forwarding the FULL original request string verbatim as the tool's argv[1] (every tool re-parses {\"<tool>\":arg} itself via parse_argument_vector_json_request). The reserved key \"help\" is intercepted and served locally. Reaching this door authorizes running any tool in available_tools; the tool name is a key resolved inside the shell's own bin, never a path.","module_name":"dispatch-capability-gated-json-request","package_name":"dispatch-capability-gated-json-request","function_definitions":{"dispatch_capability_gated_json_request":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_help","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"help"},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":">","lhs":{"value":"__argc"},"rhs":{"value":"two"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"raw","base":"__argv","index":"two","scale":8}],"branch_on_failure":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"consume-entire-content-within-stdin","invocation_